IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: to suppport the educational programs of the redwoods district by soliciting and receiving gifts.
IRS990.MissionDesc: To Support the Educational programs of the redwoods district by soliciting and receiving gifts, dispensing funds to assist students, and promotoing the general welfare of the college.
IRS990.Desc: The foundation operates a cafeteria on the college campus. The Cafeteria provides food services to students and employees of the college.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: The foundation operated a bookstore on the college campus the bookstore provides books and supplies to students and employees of the college.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: The foundation provides scholarship funds and supports various educational student programs, college teams, and clubs at the college of redwoods.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part V, Line 4: Intended uses of the endowment fund.
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Endowment funds are inteded to provide student scholarships.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Foundation reviews scholarships applications and awards the scholarships. The redwoods community college distrcit distibutes the scholarships to eligible students.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part III, Line 4d: Other Program Services Description
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 4: The foundation provides scholarship funds and supports various educational student programs, college teams, and clubs at the college of redwoods.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A draft copy is provided to each board member for review and approval during a board meeting.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: On an annual basis the conflict of interest policy is reviewed and disclosure statements are renewed.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Governing dcouments, policies, and financial statements are made availaable to the public on the foundaiton website and by request.
